Alpine World Ski Championships: Bode Miller crashes out
American Bode Miller crashes out of the men's Super G race as Hannes Reichelt makes it double gold for Austria at the 2015 Alpine World Ski Championships in Colorado.Reichelt won in a time of one minute 15.68 seconds, with Miller tearing a hamstring tendon in the crash and looking set to miss the rest of the Championships.Canada's Dustin Cook finishing second and Adrien Theaux taking the bronze medal for France, while Austria'sAnna Fenninger won goldin the women's Super Giant Slalom race earlier in the week.Click here to see live BBC Sport coverage details for the 2015 Alpine World Ski Championships.Available to UK users only.